I am a big fan of these animal simulator games. I love the variety of animals on this particular simulation. Like the other users have said, the animals get up and run away after you kill them and sometimes when they are dead the bodies start sliding away. This is a new game though so some bugs are to be expected. There are a few things I would like to suggest to better enhance the users experience; a storyline and missions will keep people playing longer. You should make it so that after you level up far enough you can keep adding to your pack. You should make us able to name the cheetahs. And have the family eat with you. When your cubs are very little I think that you should have to defend them against predators, otherwise they will be eaten. And make the blood more real. Maybe even add certin territories, like crossing the border would cause the lions to come after you. Adding just a few more graphics would really make the game more life like, such as more patches of dry grass on the ground. Maybe even add an occasional dead animal to feed on surrounded by buzzards. Nightvision should be an option too, since cats can see in the dark. Great job creating this, whoever did.
